Popular singer Oluwafemi Oladapo aka Slimcase has expressed sympathy for the 30-year sentencing of R&B singer R Kelly for sex trafficking. On an Instagram live Otumba Lamba, as he is also fondly called, said R Kelly’s song influenced his childhood but registered his dissatisfaction on the issue. He said: “I feel sorry for R Kelly, I grew up listening to R Kelly. I love R Kelly but I am not part of the abuse.    Yemi Alade eulogises Ada Ameh, shares video shoot     New ride confirms my big girl status – Cuppy     American record label welcomes Asake to fold   “Don’t abuse people, I don’t know how true that is anyways everyone has their own story with what I heard he is guilty bro. “You don’t take advantage of people just because God has blessed you and then you are talented and you have girls around you, “I have girls around me too but I don’t take advantage of people. We can just joke or play about things but I always keep a boundary. “Don’t say because you are popular you now take advantage of people, respect people.”